                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13202407" author="xedin" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 14:08:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch encapsulates truncate logic into SecondaryIndex.truncate(long) abstract method so every type of indices would be able to implement desired logic (currently implemented for KeysIndex), which also removes a good bit of code from CompactionManager.submitTruncate(...).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13202412" author="xedin" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 14:13:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;renamed CFS.truncateSSTables(long) to CFS.discardSSTables(long).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13202434" author="tjake" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 14:41:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SIM.getIndexes() should use a IdenenityHashMap since PerRowSecondaryIndexes share the same instance across rows.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13202437" author="xedin" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 14:48:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;uses IdentityHashMap in SecondaryIndexManager.getIndexes()&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13202442" author="tjake" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 14:52:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13202462" author="xedin" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 15:25:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
